files.description: This file contains the experimental data shown in Fig. 1E of the main text. The first three columns give the singles densities of the two individual spin states and the total singles density. The following three columns give the error bars for these curves. The final column is the data for the x-axis of the plot, the lattice-site index. Each column is labeled according to the color/shape of the respective points in the figure.

files.description: This file contains the experimental data shown in Fig. 2G of the main text. The first three columns give the data points, error bars, and x-axis values (the time axis) respectively for the purple squares in the figure. The following three columns give the same for the black circles in the figure. The final three columns give the same for the green diamonds in the figure. Each column is labeled according to the color/shape of the respective points, and the quantity represented (i.e. data, error bars, or time values).

files.description: This file contains the experimental data shown in Fig. 2H of the main text. The first four columns give the data points (spin current), error bars, x-axis values (gradient in the spin density), and error bars on the x-axis values respectively for the orange circles in the figure. The following four columns give the same for the red diamonds in the figure. The final four columns give the same for the blue squares in the figure. Each column is labeled according to the color/shape of the respective curve, as well as the quantity represented (i.e. data, data error bars, spin density gradient, or error bars for the spin density gradient).
files.label: Fig2H.tab

dataFile.description: This file contains the experimental data shown in Fig. 2H of the main text. The following four columns give the same for the red diamonds in the figure. The final four columns give the same for the blue squares in the figure. Each column is labeled according to the color/shape of the respective curve, as well as the quantity represented (i.e. data, data error bars, spin density gradient, or error bars for the spin density gradient).

files.description: This file contains the experimental data, the linear fit to the experimental data, and data for the NLCE and Heisenberg theoretical predictions shown in Fig. 3 of the main text. The first four columns give the experimental data, the associated error bars, the x-axis values (t/U), and the error bars for the x-axis values respectively. The following two columns give the 2D Heisenberg theoretical prediction (dashed red line) and the associated x-axis values respectively. The next two columns give the parameters for the linear fit (black dot-dashed line) to the experimental data. The final two columns give the NLCE prediction (blue solid line) and the associated x-axis values respectively. Each column is labeled according to the color/shape of the respective points in the figure, as well as the quantity represented.
files.label: Fig3.tab

files.description: This file contains the experimental data and NLCE predictions shown in the inset to Fig. S2 of the supplemental material. The first four columns give the data points (red circles), error bars, x-axis values (t/U), and error bars for the x-axis values respectively. The following two columns give the NLCE predictions (blue dot-dashed lines) for a fixed entropy per particle of 1.2 and 1.0 respectively. The final column gives the x-axis (t/U) values for these NLCE predictions. Each column is labeled according to the color/shape of the respective points, and the quantity represented (i.e. data, error bars, t/U, t/U error bars, or NLCE data).
